================================================================================
  TASK 2.2: BACKEND — Complete Drizzle Schema + Migrations
  Duration: 5 days | Week 5-6
================================================================================

  WHAT:
  Define all core database tables in Drizzle ORM, generate SQL migrations,
  apply to PostgreSQL. This is the single source of truth for backend data.
  See Part V, Section I below for complete Drizzle schema definitions.

  DRIZZLE SCHEMA TABLES (30+ tables):
  - users (id, email, display_name, logto_id, plan, timezone, avatar_url)
  - tasks (id, title, description, status, priority, due_at, energy,
    project_id, user_id, section_id, rrule, est_minutes, actual_minutes,
    is_deleted, completed_at, sort_order)
  - subtasks (id, task_id, title, is_done, sort_order, assignee_id)
  - projects (id, name, color, icon, user_id, team_id, default_view,
    description, due_at, is_archived)
  - sections (id, project_id, name, sort_order)
  - tags (id, name, color, user_id)
  - task_tags (task_id, tag_id) — many-to-many join
  - comments (id, task_id, user_id, body, created_at)
  - attachments (id, task_id, url, filename, mime_type, size_bytes)
  - recurring_rules (id, task_id, rrule_str, next_at, last_generated_at)
  - reminders (id, task_id, channel, offset_minutes, sent_at, status)
  - notification_channels (id, user_id, type, identifier, verified,
    preferences, connected_at)
  - notification_log (id, user_id, channel, template_id, status, sent_at,
    error_message, message_id)
  - daily_content (id, category, text, author, source, language, metadata)
  - user_content_prefs (user_id, category, deliver_at, is_active)
  - content_delivery_log (id, user_id, content_id, delivered_at, channel)
  - rituals (id, user_id, type, mood, gratitude_text, intention_text,
    reflection_text, completed_at, date)
  - streaks (id, user_id, current, longest, last_active_date, freeze_used,
    freeze_available)
  - progress_snapshots (id, user_id, date, tasks_created, tasks_completed,
    focus_minutes, habits_done, pomodoros_completed)
  - pomodoro_sessions (id, user_id, task_id, duration_seconds,
    focus_rating, ambient_sound, started_at, completed_at)
  - sync_metadata (entity_type, user_id, last_sync_at, last_pull_at)
  - teams (id, name, owner_id, plan, logo_url, created_at)
  - team_members (team_id, user_id, role, joined_at, status)
  - gamification_xp (id, user_id, amount, source, source_id, earned_at)
  - achievements (id, user_id, achievement_key, unlocked_at, metadata)
  - task_templates (id, name, description, fields_json, subtasks_json,
    category, is_system, user_id, industry_mode)
  - feature_flags (id, name, description, enabled_pct, targeting_json,
    created_at, updated_at)
  - audit_log (id, user_id, action, resource_type, resource_id,
    details_json, ip_address, user_agent, created_at)
  - user_settings (user_id, key, value_json)
  - accountability_partners (id, user_id, partner_user_id, status,
    created_at)

  INDEXES (critical for query performance):
  - tasks: (user_id, status, due_at) — composite B-tree for my active tasks
  - tasks: (project_id, status) — project listing
  - tasks: GIN index on to_tsvector(title || description) — full-text search
  - daily_content: (category, id) — random selection per category
  - notification_log: (user_id, channel, sent_at) — daily quota counting
  - progress_snapshots: UNIQUE (user_id, date) — one per day
  - streaks: UNIQUE (user_id)
  - recurring_rules: (next_at) — BullMQ cron picks upcoming
  - audit_log: (user_id, created_at) — admin audit trail
  - gamification_xp: (user_id, earned_at) — XP aggregation

  SUB-TASKS:
  2.2.1  Create apps/backend/src/db/schema/ directory with one file per table
  2.2.2  Define all table schemas with Drizzle pgTable()
  2.2.3  Add relations via Drizzle relations() API
  2.2.4  Add Zod validation schemas (drizzle-zod) for insert/select
  2.2.5  Generate initial migration: drizzle-kit generate
  2.2.6  Apply migration to PostgreSQL: drizzle-kit migrate
  2.2.7  Write seed script (scripts/seed.ts):
         - 10 daily_content entries per category (100 total for 10 categories)
         - 5 system task_templates
         - 1 test user with 20 sample tasks across 3 projects
  2.2.8  Run seed and verify data in pgAdmin
  2.2.9  Write Vitest tests for schema validation (20+ tests)

  BACKEND PACKAGES:
  - drizzle-orm 0.36+, drizzle-kit 0.30+, drizzle-zod 0.5+
  - @paralleldrive/cuid2 (collision-resistant IDs)
  - rrule 2.8+ (RFC 5545 recurrence parsing)

  DSA USED:
  - B-tree indexes: O(log n) lookup for PK/FK queries
  - GIN (Generalized Inverted Index): Full-text search, O(k) where k=terms
  - Composite indexes: Multi-column covering indexes avoid table scans
  - Hash indexes: Exact-match on enum columns (status, priority)


================================================================================
  TASK 2.3: BACKEND - Logto Auth Integration
  Duration: 3 days | Week 6
================================================================================

  WHAT:
  Integrate Logto OIDC for authentication. Backend validates JWT via JWKS.
  Flutter uses logto_dart_sdk for sign-in/sign-up.

  API ENDPOINTS:
  POST   /api/v1/auth/callback      - Exchange auth code for tokens
  POST   /api/v1/auth/refresh       - Refresh access token
  POST   /api/v1/auth/logout        - Revoke tokens
  GET    /api/v1/auth/me            - Get current user profile
  POST   /api/v1/auth/forgot-pass   - Send password reset email
  POST   /api/v1/auth/reset-pass    - Reset password with token

  SUB-TASKS:
  2.3.1  Configure Logto app in admin console (localhost:3002):
         - App type: Native (Flutter)
         - Redirect URI: com.metaminds.unjynx://callback
         - Post-logout URI: com.metaminds.unjynx://logout
         - Enable connectors: Google, Apple, Email (Mailpit SMTP for dev)
  2.3.2  Backend auth middleware (src/middleware/auth.ts):
         - Fetch JWKS from Logto OIDC endpoint
         - Cache JWKS with 1-hour TTL (jose library, LRU cache)
         - Validate JWT: issuer, audience, expiry, RS256 signature
         - Extract claims (sub, email, name), attach to Hono context
  2.3.3  User sync on first login:
         - Valid JWT + no user record = create in users table
         - Existing user = update last_login
  2.3.4  Implement auth route handlers (src/routes/auth.ts)
  2.3.5  Flutter: Add logto_dart_sdk to mobile/pubspec.yaml
  2.3.6  Flutter: Create AuthService:
         - LogtoClient init, signIn(), signOut(), getAccessToken()
         - isAuthenticated stream for reactive auth state
  2.3.7  Flutter: Create AuthNotifier (Riverpod AsyncNotifier):
         - Wraps AuthService, provides auth state app-wide
         - Auto-redirect: unauthenticated -> Login, authenticated -> Home
  2.3.8  Flutter: Update go_router with auth redirect guard
  2.3.9  Flutter: Build Login screen (A2) - Google, Apple, Email buttons
  2.3.10 Flutter: Build Forgot Password screen (A3)
  2.3.11 Backend auth tests (10+ Vitest tests)
  2.3.12 Flutter auth integration tests (5+ tests)

  BACKEND PACKAGES: jose 5.x (JWT/JWKS), hono/bearer-auth
  FLUTTER PACKAGES: logto_dart_sdk 3.x, flutter_secure_storage 9.x,
                    flutter_web_auth_2 4.x

  SECURITY:
  - Access tokens: 15 min expiry, stored in memory only
  - Refresh tokens: flutter_secure_storage (iOS Keychain / Android Keystore)
  - PKCE (S256) for auth code flow
  - No secrets in client code
  - Rate limit: 10 req/min per IP on /auth/* endpoints

  DSA: HMAC-SHA256/RS256 (JWT signing), PKCE S256 (challenge-response),
       LRU Cache with TTL (JWKS caching)

================================================================================
  TASK 2.4: BACKEND - Complete Task CRUD REST API
  Duration: 5 days | Week 6-7
================================================================================

  WHAT:
  Full task management API with subtasks, tags, bulk operations, recurrence,
  and sync. Follows REST conventions from API-DESIGN-GUIDE.doc.

  API ENDPOINTS:

  TASKS:
  GET    /api/v1/tasks                  - List (filters, cursor pagination)
  POST   /api/v1/tasks                  - Create task
  GET    /api/v1/tasks/:id              - Get by ID
  PATCH  /api/v1/tasks/:id              - Update fields
  DELETE /api/v1/tasks/:id              - Soft-delete
  POST   /api/v1/tasks/bulk             - Bulk create (max 50)
  PATCH  /api/v1/tasks/bulk             - Bulk update (max 50)
  DELETE /api/v1/tasks/bulk             - Bulk soft-delete
  POST   /api/v1/tasks/:id/complete     - Mark complete
  POST   /api/v1/tasks/:id/uncomplete   - Revert completion
  POST   /api/v1/tasks/:id/snooze       - Snooze (body: { minutes })
  POST   /api/v1/tasks/:id/move         - Move to project
  POST   /api/v1/tasks/:id/duplicate    - Duplicate
  GET    /api/v1/tasks/:id/activity     - Activity log

  SUBTASKS:
  GET    /api/v1/tasks/:id/subtasks              - List
  POST   /api/v1/tasks/:id/subtasks              - Create
  PATCH  /api/v1/tasks/:id/subtasks/:subId       - Update
  DELETE /api/v1/tasks/:id/subtasks/:subId       - Delete
  POST   /api/v1/tasks/:id/subtasks/reorder      - Reorder

  PROJECTS:
  GET    /api/v1/projects                        - List user projects
  POST   /api/v1/projects                        - Create
  GET    /api/v1/projects/:id                    - Get detail
  PATCH  /api/v1/projects/:id                    - Update
  DELETE /api/v1/projects/:id                    - Archive/delete
  GET    /api/v1/projects/:id/tasks              - List project tasks
  POST   /api/v1/projects/:id/sections           - Create section
  PATCH  /api/v1/projects/:id/sections/:secId    - Update section
  DELETE /api/v1/projects/:id/sections/:secId    - Delete section

  TAGS:
  GET    /api/v1/tags       - List user tags
  POST   /api/v1/tags       - Create
  PATCH  /api/v1/tags/:id   - Update
  DELETE /api/v1/tags/:id   - Delete

  RECURRING:
  GET    /api/v1/tasks/:id/recurrence    - Get rule
  PUT    /api/v1/tasks/:id/recurrence    - Set/update
  DELETE /api/v1/tasks/:id/recurrence    - Remove
  GET    /api/v1/tasks/:id/occurrences   - Preview next N

  SYNC:
  POST   /api/v1/sync/push     - Push local changes (SyncRecord[])
  POST   /api/v1/sync/pull     - Pull changes since timestamp
  GET    /api/v1/sync/status   - Sync status per entity type

  QUERY PARAMETERS (GET /api/v1/tasks):
  status=pending|completed|all, priority=p1|p2|p3|p4 (comma-sep),
  energy=low|medium|high|peak, project_id, tag_id (comma-sep),
  due_before (ISO 8601), due_after (ISO 8601), search (full-text),
  sort=due_at|priority|created_at|title (prefix - for desc),
  cursor (opaque Base64), limit (default 50, max 200)

  RESPONSE ENVELOPE:
  { "data": [...], "meta": { "cursor": "...", "has_more": true, "total": N } }

  ERROR FORMAT (RFC 9457):
  { "type": "https://api.unjynx.com/errors/...", "title": "...",
    "status": 422, "detail": "...", "instance": "/api/v1/...",
    "errors": [{ "field": "...", "message": "..." }] }

  SUB-TASKS:
  2.4.1  Create route files: src/routes/tasks.ts, subtasks.ts, projects.ts,
         tags.ts, recurring.ts, sync.ts
  2.4.2  Repository layer: src/repositories/task.repository.ts,
         project.repository.ts, tag.repository.ts, subtask.repository.ts
  2.4.3  Service layer: src/services/task.service.ts,
         project.service.ts, recurrence.service.ts, sync.service.ts
  2.4.4  Cursor-based pagination utility:
         Encode (id, sort_value) as opaque Base64 cursor
         WHERE (sort_col, id) > (cursor_sort, cursor_id) ORDER BY sort_col, id
  2.4.5  Full-text search with PostgreSQL tsvector + pg_trgm
  2.4.6  RRULE expansion: on complete generate next, preview next 5
  2.4.7  Sync endpoints matching service_sync Flutter package:
         POST /sync/push: receive SyncRecord[], merge with LWW, return ack
         POST /sync/pull: return records changed since timestamp
  2.4.8  Idempotency-Key header for POST/PATCH
  2.4.9  Rate limiting middleware (Valkey sliding window):
         100 req/min authenticated, 20 req/min unauthenticated
         Headers: X-RateLimit-Limit, X-RateLimit-Remaining, X-RateLimit-Reset
  2.4.10 ETag/If-None-Match for conditional GET responses
  2.4.11 Write Vitest tests (40+ covering all operations, errors, edge cases)

  DSA USED:
  - Cursor pagination: O(log n) with B-tree (vs O(n) for OFFSET)
  - RRULE FSM: O(1) per occurrence generation (rrule.js, full RFC 5545)
  - Trie-based fuzzy search: pg_trgm GIN index, O(k) where k=query length
  - Sliding window rate limiter: Valkey ZRANGEBYSCORE, O(log n) operations
  - LWW-Register CRDT: O(f) merge where f=number of fields per record

  BACKEND PACKAGES: @hono/zod-validator, rrule 2.8+

