SCREEN F3: POMODORO TIMER SCREEN (Free — all tiers)
Phase: 2
─────────────────────────────────────────

  PURPOSE:
    Full-screen focus mode. Large circular timer (25 min work / 5 min break,
    configurable). Current task displayed. Session counter. Ambient sounds.
    Minimizes to floating bubble when navigating away. Post-session feedback
    + auto-log time to task. Game Mode XP integration (if enabled).

  FRONTEND (Flutter):
    Package: feature_todos (or feature_focus)
    Route: /focus/pomodoro (or modal overlay)
    Key Widgets:
      - PomodoroTimer — large circular countdown timer (CustomPainter arc)
        - Work: 25 min default (configurable 15/20/25/30/45/60)
        - Break: 5 min short, 15 min long (every 4th session)
      - CurrentTaskCard — displays the task being focused on (title + priority)
      - SessionCounter — "Pomodoro 3 of 4" text with dot indicators
      - TimerControls — Start (gold) | Pause (outline) | Reset (muted)
      - AmbientSoundSelector — horizontal scrollable:
        Rain | Forest | Cafe | Lo-fi | Ocean | Silence (each with icon)
      - FloatingBubble — overlay widget when user navigates away:
        Small circle showing remaining time, tappable to return
      - PostSessionSheet — bottom sheet after completion:
        - "How focused were you?" slider (1-5 stars)
        - Time auto-logged to task
        - Focus ring fill + completion feedback
        - XP earned (only if Game Mode on, e.g., "+15 XP")
    State Management:
      - pomodoroProvider (StateNotifier<PomodoroState>) — timer state machine
        States: idle → running → paused → breakTime → completed
        Fields: currentSeconds, totalSeconds, sessionsCompleted, isBreak
      - ambientSoundProvider (StateProvider<AmbientSound>) — selected sound
      - focusTaskProvider (StateProvider<Task?>) — task being focused on
      - focusHistoryProvider (AsyncNotifier) — logs completed Pomodoro sessions
    Packages (pub.dev):
      - audioplayers ^6.0.0 — ambient sound playback (local assets)
      - flutter_overlay_window ^0.4.0 — floating bubble (Android)
        (iOS: PiP not available for non-video, use local notification instead)
    Drift Tables (local):
      - focus_sessions — log: taskId, duration, rating, completedAt
      - todos — update timeSpent field after session

  BACKEND (Hono/TypeScript):
    Endpoints:
      POST /api/v1/focus/sessions
        Request: { taskId: string, duration: number, rating: 1-5,
                   sessionsCompleted: number, type: "pomodoro"|"freeform" }
        Response: { session: FocusSession, xpEarned?: number }
        Notes: XP calculated server-side if Game Mode enabled

      GET /api/v1/focus/stats
        Query: ?range=7d|30d|90d
        Response: { totalMinutes: number, avgRating: number,
                    sessionsCount: number, byDay: DailyFocusStats[] }

    Business Logic:
      - Timer runs client-side (no server pinging during focus)
      - Session logged to server only on completion (not on pause/abandon)
      - Abandoned sessions (< 50% completed) not logged (prevent gaming)
      - XP: 10 XP per completed Pomodoro + 5 bonus for 5-star focus rating
      - Ambient sounds: bundled assets (no streaming), ~2MB total
      - Floating bubble: Android overlay permission required (prompted once)

  DATA FLOW:
    User selects task → opens Pomodoro → taps Start → timer counts down →
    pomodoroProvider ticks every second → on complete: haptic + sound →
    PostSessionSheet appears → user rates focus → POST /focus/sessions →
    Drift insert focus_sessions + update todo.timeSpent → return to task list

  INTERACTIONS & ANIMATIONS:
    - Timer arc: smooth countdown, arc shrinks (CustomPainter repaint every 1s)
    - Start: gold button pulses once then stays solid
    - Complete: timer ring fills gold → burst particles → haptic heavy + chime sound
    - Break transition: work ring fades → break ring appears (green) (500ms crossfade)
    - Session dots: fill gold sequentially as sessions complete
    - Ambient sound: fade in over 2s when selected, crossfade when switching
    - Floating bubble: subtle pulse animation (scale 1.0→1.05, 2s loop)
    - Focus rating: stars fill with staggered animation (100ms per star)

  ACCESSIBILITY:
    - Timer announces remaining time every 5 minutes (screen reader)
    - Controls have large tap targets (min 48x48)
    - Ambient sounds have visual equalizer indicator for deaf users
    - Haptic feedback on complete (important for visually impaired)

  TESTS (target count):
    - Unit: 6 (timer countdown, session tracking, break logic, XP calculation,
      abandoned session rejection, time logging to task)
    - Widget: 6 (timer renders, controls work, ambient selector, session counter,
      post-session sheet, floating bubble)
    - Integration: 2 (full pomodoro cycle, focus stats accumulation)


SCREEN J1: CHANNEL HUB SCREEN (Free — settings)
Phase: 3
─────────────────────────────────────────

  PURPOSE:
    Central management for all notification channels. Shows connection status
    for: Push, Telegram (Free), Email (Free), WhatsApp (Pro), SMS (Pro),
    Instagram (Pro), Slack (Pro), Discord (Pro). Each channel expandable to
    show details, test message, quiet hours, digest mode, fallback order.

  FRONTEND (Flutter):
    Package: feature_channels
    Route: /settings/channels (or /channels)
    Key Widgets:
      - ChannelHubList — ListView of ChannelCard widgets (one per channel)
      - ChannelCard — expandable card per channel:
        - Icon + name + connection status badge (green/gray/red)
        - Tier badge (Free/Pro) — Pro channels show lock icon if user is Free
        - Expanded view:
          - ConnectionStatus — "Connected since [date]" or "Not connected"
          - LastMessageInfo — "Last reminder sent: [time]"
          - TestMessageButton — "Send me a test reminder" → sends via API
          - QuietHoursToggle — per-channel override (start/end time pickers)
          - DigestModeToggle — batch notifications for this channel
          - FallbackOrderInfo — "If this fails, try: [next channel]"
          - DisconnectButton — red, with confirmation dialog
      - ConnectButton — per channel: routes to J2/J3/J4/J6 connection flows
      - UpgradePrompt — shown inline for Pro channels when user is Free:
        "Unlock WhatsApp reminders with Pro" + upgrade CTA
    State Management:
      - channelListProvider (AsyncNotifier<List<Channel>>) — all channels + status
      - channelStatusProvider (family, per channel) — real-time connection status
      - testMessageProvider (AsyncNotifier) — send test message state
    Packages (pub.dev):
      - (standard Flutter widgets)
    Drift Tables (local):
      - notification_channels — channel type, status, config, lastMessageAt

  BACKEND (Hono/TypeScript):
    Endpoints:
      GET /api/v1/channels
        Response: { channels: Channel[] }
        Channel: { type, status: "connected"|"disconnected"|"error",
                   connectedAt?, lastMessageAt?, config: ChannelConfig }

      POST /api/v1/channels/:type/test
        Response: { sent: boolean, messageId?: string, error?: string }
        Notes: Sends a test reminder via the specified channel

      DELETE /api/v1/channels/:type
        Response: { disconnected: true }
        Notes: Revokes tokens/unsubscribes. Consent records retained for compliance.

    Business Logic:
      - Channel status checked in real-time via WebSocket events
      - Test message: sends "This is a test from UNJYNX!" with task-like formatting
      - Disconnect: per channel — Telegram: deactivate bot, WhatsApp: opt-out,
        Instagram: unfollow, SMS: STOP, Slack/Discord: revoke OAuth
      - Free users see all channels but Pro ones show upgrade CTA
      - Fallback chain managed in J5 (notification preferences)

  DATA FLOW:
    ChannelHub loads → channelListProvider fetches channels from Drift (local) +
    API sync → renders ChannelCard list → user taps "Connect" → routes to J2/J3/J4/J6 →
    on return: channel status updated via WebSocket → card refreshes →
    user taps "Test" → testMessageProvider sends test → success/error shown

  INTERACTIONS & ANIMATIONS:
    - Card expand: smooth height animation (250ms, easeInOut)
    - Status badge: green pulse when connected (subtle, 3s period)
    - Test message: button shows loading spinner → checkmark on success (300ms)
    - Disconnect: confirmation dialog → card status animates to gray (200ms)
    - Pro lock icon: subtle shimmer effect on hover/focus
    - Upgrade CTA: gold gradient background with slight glow

  ACCESSIBILITY:
    - Status announced: "Telegram: Connected" or "WhatsApp: Not connected, Pro required"
    - Test message result announced: "Test message sent successfully"
    - Expand/collapse: announced as "expanded"/"collapsed"

  TESTS (target count):
    - Unit: 6 (channel list loading, status mapping, test message logic,
      disconnect flow, tier gating, fallback display)
    - Widget: 6 (all 8 channel cards render, expand/collapse, test button,
      Pro lock display, upgrade CTA, disconnect confirmation)
    - Integration: 2 (full hub load + test message, connect flow round-trip)


SCREEN J2: TELEGRAM CONNECTION FLOW (Free)
Phase: 3
─────────────────────────────────────────

  PURPOSE:
    Connect Telegram for free reminders. Shows QR code + deep link to UNJYNX bot.
    User opens Telegram, taps Start, bot confirms connection. App updates status
    in real-time via WebSocket. Inline keyboard interactions on reminders:
    [Mark Done] [Snooze 1hr] [View Task].

  FRONTEND (Flutter):
    Package: feature_channels
    Route: /channels/telegram/connect
    Key Widgets:
      - TelegramInstructions — step-by-step guide with illustrations
      - QrCodeDisplay — QR code encoding t.me/UNJYNXBot?start=[USER_TOKEN]
        (generated client-side from user's connection token)
      - DeepLinkButton — "Open Telegram" button → launches t.me deep link
      - ConnectionWaiting — animated loading state: "Waiting for you to tap Start..."
        with pulsing Telegram icon
      - ConnectionSuccess — green checkmark + "Connected!" + test message button
      - TestReminderButton — sends sample reminder with inline keyboard buttons
    State Management:
      - telegramConnectionProvider (AsyncNotifier) — state machine:
        States: instructions → waitingForBot → connected → testSent
      - connectionTokenProvider — generates one-time token for bot deep link
      - webSocketListenerProvider — listens for "telegram_connected" event
    Packages (pub.dev):
      - qr_flutter ^4.1.0 — QR code generation
      - url_launcher ^6.3.0 — deep link to Telegram
    Drift Tables (local):
      - notification_channels — Telegram connection status + botChatId

  BACKEND (Hono/TypeScript):
    Endpoints:
      POST /api/v1/channels/telegram/token
        Response: { token: string, deepLink: string, expiresIn: 300 }
        Notes: One-time token, 5-minute expiry

      Webhook: POST /api/v1/webhooks/telegram (Telegram Bot API callback)
        Handles: /start command with token → validates → links user to chat
        Sends WebSocket event: { type: "channel_connected", channel: "telegram" }

      POST /api/v1/channels/telegram/test
        Response: { sent: true, messageId: string }

    Business Logic:
      - Bot: @UNJYNXBot registered via Telegram BotFather
      - /start [token]: validates token, stores chatId for user, marks connected
      - Inline keyboards on reminders: [✅ Done] [⏰ Snooze 1hr] [👀 View]
      - Callback queries: bot handles button taps → updates task status via API
      - Rate limit: Telegram allows 30 messages/second per bot (generous)
      - Cost: $0 (Telegram Bot API is completely free)

  DATA FLOW:
    User opens J2 → POST /telegram/token → token generated → QR code + deep link
    shown → user opens Telegram → taps /start → Telegram webhook fires →
    server validates token → stores chatId → WebSocket "telegram_connected" →
    Flutter updates to ConnectionSuccess → user taps Test → sample message sent

  INTERACTIONS & ANIMATIONS:
    - QR code: appears with fade-in (300ms)
    - Waiting state: Telegram icon pulses (scale 1.0→1.1, 1s loop) + dots animation
    - Connected: green checkmark drops in with spring animation + confetti burst
    - Deep link button: Telegram blue color with icon
    - Test message: loading → success checkmark (300ms)

  ACCESSIBILITY:
    - QR code has text alternative: deep link URL selectable/copyable
    - Steps announced sequentially by screen reader
    - Connection success announced: "Telegram connected successfully"

  TESTS (target count):
    - Unit: 5 (token generation, deep link formatting, webhook validation,
      chatId storage, connection state machine)
    - Widget: 4 (QR renders, deep link button, waiting state, success state)
    - Integration: 2 (full connection flow with mock webhook, test message)


SCREEN J3: WHATSAPP CONNECTION FLOW (Pro)
Phase: 3
─────────────────────────────────────────

  PURPOSE:
    Connect WhatsApp reminders (Pro only). Phone number input with country code,
    OTP verification (via WhatsApp message or SMS), consent screen (TRAI/TCPA
    compliant), confirmation template sent. Interactive buttons on reminders:
    [Mark Done] [Snooze 1hr] [View Task]. Daily digest option.

  FRONTEND (Flutter):
    Package: feature_channels
    Route: /channels/whatsapp/connect
    Key Widgets:
      - ProGateCheck — if user is Free, show upgrade prompt instead of flow
      - PhoneInput — phone number field with country code dropdown
        Default country: auto-detected from device locale
      - OtpVerification — 6-digit input sent via WhatsApp (fallback: SMS)
        60s countdown for resend, max 3 retries
      - ConsentScreen — legal text:
        "UNJYNX will send task reminders and daily content to this number.
         You can opt out anytime by replying STOP."
        + checkbox "I agree" + "Connect" button
      - WhatsAppConnected — success state:
        - Green checkmark + "Connected!"
        - Test message button
        - Daily digest toggle: "Send all tasks + content in one morning message"
      - InteractiveButtonPreview — shows sample reminder with button layout
    State Management:
      - whatsappConnectionProvider (AsyncNotifier) — state machine:
        States: proCheck → phoneInput → otpSent → verifying → consent → connected
      - otpTimerProvider — 60s countdown for resend
      - dailyDigestProvider (StateProvider<bool>) — digest toggle
    Packages (pub.dev):
      - intl_phone_number_input ^0.7.4 — country code picker + validation
    Drift Tables (local):
      - notification_channels — WhatsApp connection status + phone number (encrypted)

  BACKEND (Hono/TypeScript):
    Endpoints:
      POST /api/v1/channels/whatsapp/send-otp
        Request: { phoneNumber: string, countryCode: string }
        Response: { otpSent: true, method: "whatsapp"|"sms", expiresIn: 60 }
        Notes: Sends OTP via WhatsApp first. If user not on WhatsApp, falls back to SMS.
               India: Gupshup BSP. International: Twilio WhatsApp API.

      POST /api/v1/channels/whatsapp/verify-otp
        Request: { phoneNumber: string, code: string }
        Response: { verified: true }

      POST /api/v1/channels/whatsapp/consent
        Request: { phoneNumber: string, consented: true, consentTimestamp: string }
        Response: { channelId: string, connected: true }
        Notes: Stores consent record. Sends confirmation template message.

      POST /api/v1/channels/whatsapp/test
        Response: { sent: true, messageId: string }

      PUT /api/v1/channels/whatsapp/digest
        Request: { enabled: boolean, time: "08:00" }
        Response: { updated: true }

    Business Logic:
      - OTP: 6 digits, 60s expiry, max 3 attempts
      - Consent: mandatory for TCPA/TRAI compliance. Record stored with timestamp.
      - Confirmation template: pre-approved WhatsApp template message
      - Interactive buttons: WhatsApp Business API interactive message type
        [✅ Mark Done] [⏰ Snooze 1hr] [👀 View Task]
      - STOP keyword: mandatory unsubscribe, deletes channel (compliance)
      - Daily digest: BullMQ job at configured time, batches all tasks + content
      - Cost: per-template-message (Jan 2026 pricing). India via Gupshup (~cheapest).
      - 24h conversation window: opened by template, user reply extends it

  DATA FLOW:
    User opens J3 → Pro check → phone input → POST /whatsapp/send-otp → OTP sent →
    user enters code → POST /whatsapp/verify-otp → consent screen → POST /consent →
    confirmation WhatsApp template sent → WebSocket "whatsapp_connected" →
    success state → optional: toggle daily digest

  INTERACTIONS & ANIMATIONS:
    - Pro gate: if Free, shows gold upgrade card with "Unlock WhatsApp" CTA
    - OTP input: auto-focuses next digit on input (6 separate fields)
    - OTP countdown: circular timer shrinking (60s)
    - Consent checkbox: gold fill animation (150ms)
    - Connected: WhatsApp green checkmark + phone number displayed
    - Test message: loading spinner → "Sent!" with checkmark (300ms)

  ACCESSIBILITY:
    - Phone input: country code announced by screen reader
    - OTP: each digit field labeled ("Digit 1 of 6")
    - Consent text: full legal text readable by screen reader
    - Connected state: "WhatsApp connected to [phone number]"

  TESTS (target count):
    - Unit: 6 (phone validation, OTP flow, consent storage, STOP handling,
      digest scheduling, Pro gate check)
    - Widget: 6 (Pro gate, phone input, OTP verification, consent screen,
      connected state, digest toggle)
    - Integration: 2 (full connection flow, test message delivery)


SCREEN J4: INSTAGRAM FRIEND FIRST FLOW (Pro)
Phase: 3
─────────────────────────────────────────

  PURPOSE:
    Connect Instagram reminders via "Friend First" approach. User provides
    username → UNJYNX sends follow request from @UNJYNX → user accepts →
    UNJYNX sends initial DM "Reply START" → user replies → 24h messaging
    window opens. Daily content keeps window alive. Push notification if
    window expires.

  FRONTEND (Flutter):
    Package: feature_channels
    Route: /channels/instagram/connect
    Key Widgets:
      - ProGateCheck — upgrade prompt if Free user
      - InstagramExplainer — illustration explaining Friend First approach:
        "We'll send a follow request from @UNJYNX. Accept it, then reply START."
      - UsernameInput — Instagram username field with @-prefix
      - FollowRequestSent — status: "Follow request sent to @[username]"
        "Accept our request, then reply START to our DM."
        Animated waiting indicator with Instagram gradient icon
      - WaitingForReply — "Waiting for your START reply..."
        Shows mock DM conversation preview
      - InstagramConnected — success: "Instagram connected! You'll get reminders here."
        Daily content toggle: "Keep your messaging window alive with daily content"
      - WindowExpiredWarning — if 24h window expires, shows reconnect instructions
    State Management:
      - instagramConnectionProvider (AsyncNotifier) — state machine:
        States: proCheck → usernameInput → followSent → waitingForStart →
                connected → windowExpired
      - instagramWindowProvider — tracks 24h messaging window status
      - webSocketListenerProvider — listens for "instagram_connected" event
    Packages (pub.dev):
      - url_launcher ^6.3.0 — open Instagram app/web to accept follow request
    Drift Tables (local):
      - notification_channels — Instagram status + username + windowExpiresAt

  BACKEND (Hono/TypeScript):
    Endpoints:
      POST /api/v1/channels/instagram/follow
        Request: { username: string }
        Response: { followRequestSent: true }
        Notes: Uses Instagram Graph API / Messenger API to send follow request
               from @UNJYNX business account

      Webhook: POST /api/v1/webhooks/instagram (Messenger API callback)
        Handles: "START" message → validates username → links user → opens window
        Sends WebSocket event: { type: "channel_connected", channel: "instagram" }

      POST /api/v1/channels/instagram/test
        Response: { sent: true }
        Notes: Only works within 24h window

      GET /api/v1/channels/instagram/window-status
        Response: { active: boolean, expiresAt: string, hoursRemaining: number }

    Business Logic:
      - Friend First: Instagram Messenger API requires user-initiated conversation
        or mutual follow for DMs. We follow first, user accepts, user replies START.
      - 24h messaging window: each user message/reaction resets the 24h clock
      - Daily content: sent as Instagram DM to keep window alive (user reacts = reset)
      - Window expired: push notification "Your Instagram reminders paused.
        Open Instagram and message @UNJYNX to reconnect."
      - BullMQ job: checks window expiry every hour, sends push notification if expired
      - Cost: Instagram Messenger API is free (within Facebook/Meta policies)
      - Limitation: AI chatbot restriction — messages must be task-specific, not general AI

  DATA FLOW:
    User opens J4 → Pro check → username input → POST /instagram/follow →
    follow request sent → user accepts on Instagram → user sends "START" DM →
    Instagram webhook fires → server validates → WebSocket "instagram_connected" →
    Flutter updates to connected → daily content sent to keep window alive →
    BullMQ monitors window → if expired: push notification to reconnect

  INTERACTIONS & ANIMATIONS:
    - Instagram gradient: username input has Instagram gradient border (animated shimmer)
    - Follow sent: Instagram icon with checkmark, pulsing (1s loop)
    - Waiting for START: mock DM conversation bubbles animate in sequence
    - Connected: Instagram gradient burst + "Connected!" text
    - Window timer: shows "Window active: 23h 14m remaining" with countdown
    - Window expired: card turns amber with "Reconnect" button

  ACCESSIBILITY:
    - Explainer: illustrations have alt text describing Friend First process
    - Status transitions announced by screen reader
    - Reconnect instructions clear and actionable

  TESTS (target count):
    - Unit: 5 (username validation, follow request, webhook handling,
      window tracking, expiry notification)
    - Widget: 5 (Pro gate, username input, waiting states, connected,
      window expired warning)
    - Integration: 2 (full connection flow with mock webhook, window expiry flow)


