      - schedule_suggestions — cached AI suggestions
      - todos — update scheduledAt after acceptance

  BACKEND (Hono/TypeScript):
    Endpoints:
      POST /api/v1/ai/schedule/suggest
        Request: { taskIds?: string[], dateRange: { start, end } }
        Response: { suggestions: ScheduleSuggestion[] }
        ScheduleSuggestion: { taskId, suggestedStart, suggestedEnd, reason,
                              confidence: 0-1, conflicts: CalendarEvent[] }
        Notes: Uses Claude Sonnet for scheduling logic. Considers:
               - Task priority + deadline urgency
               - Calendar events (Google Calendar sync)
               - Historical productivity patterns (by hour/day)
               - Energy level predictions
               - Duration estimates (learned from past similar tasks)

      POST /api/v1/ai/schedule/accept
        Request: { acceptedSuggestions: { taskId, start, end }[] }
        Response: { scheduled: number, tasks: Task[] }

      POST /api/v1/ai/schedule/undo
        Response: { reverted: number }
        Notes: Restores previous scheduledAt values from snapshot

    Business Logic:
      - Scheduling algorithm: constraint satisfaction + user preference learning
      - Conflict detection: checks Google Calendar + existing task blocks
      - Duration estimation: moving average of actual time for similar tasks
      - Confidence score: higher if more data available, lower for new task types
      - Undo: stores pre-schedule snapshot, full revert possible within 24h
      - Cost: ~$0.01 per schedule request (Sonnet, medium context)

  DATA FLOW:
    User opens K2 → POST /ai/schedule/suggest → AI analyzes tasks + calendar +
    patterns → returns suggestions → SchedulePreview renders with dashed blocks →
    user reviews/drags to adjust → taps "Accept All" or individual accept →
    POST /ai/schedule/accept → todos updated with scheduledAt → calendar view reflects

  INTERACTIONS & ANIMATIONS:
    - AI thinking: calendar shimmers with gold particles while generating
    - Suggestions appear: task blocks slide into calendar slots (staggered, 100ms each)
    - Dashed border: animated dash pattern (marching ants, 2s cycle)
    - Accept: dashed border solidifies (300ms transition)
    - Conflict: red pulse on overlapping area
    - Undo: all blocks slide back to unscheduled sidebar (reverse animation)

  TESTS (target count):
    - Unit: 5 (suggestion generation, conflict detection, duration estimation,
      acceptance flow, undo/snapshot)
    - Widget: 4 (preview renders, drag adjustment, accept/undo buttons, conflict indicator)
    - Integration: 2 (full suggest-accept flow, undo flow)


SCREEN K3: AI INSIGHTS SCREEN (Pro — v2 deferred)
Phase: v2
─────────────────────────────────────────

  PURPOSE:
    (v2 — deferred) Weekly auto-generated AI productivity report. Summary stats,
    pattern detection, actionable suggestions, week-over-week comparisons,
