        }

      POST /api/v1/ai/insights/generate (internal, BullMQ trigger)
        Notes: Generates weekly insight for all Pro users. Runs Sunday 8pm user timezone.
               Uses Claude Sonnet to analyze task data and generate natural language insights.

    Business Logic:
      - BullMQ cron: every Sunday 8pm per user timezone → gathers week's task data
      - Claude Sonnet: generates natural language insights from structured data
      - Pattern detection: aggregates by day-of-week, hour-of-day, project, tag
      - Predictions: linear regression on completion rates per project
      - Warnings: flags tasks deferred 3+ times, overdue 7+ days, projects stalled
      - Suggestions: based on patterns (e.g., "you complete 40% more tasks on Wednesdays")
      - Cost: ~$0.005 per weekly report (Sonnet, medium context)
      - Caching: generated once, served from cache until next week

  DATA FLOW:
    Sunday 8pm → BullMQ job triggers → aggregates user's week data → POST to Claude
    Sonnet → parses AI response → stores WeeklyInsight → push notification: "Your
    weekly report is ready" → user opens K3 → weeklyInsightsProvider loads from
    API/cache → renders all sections

