# SYSTEM 1: ADMIN PANEL UI SPECIFICATION
## UNJYNX Admin Dashboard (React + Refine on Vercel)

### 1.1 TECHNOLOGY STACK

- Framework: Refine v4+ (headless React admin framework)
- UI Library: Ant Design 5.x (best Refine integration, enterprise-ready components)
- Data Provider: Custom REST data provider connecting to Hono backend
- Auth Provider: Logto OIDC integration (same as app, separate admin OIDC app)
- Access Control: Refine's built-in accessControlProvider with Casbin policies
- State Management: React Query (built into Refine)
- Charts: Apache ECharts (via echarts-for-react) for analytics dashboards
- Tables: Ant Design ProTable with server-side pagination/filtering/sorting
- Deployment: Vercel (static build, API calls to backend)
- Audit Logging: Refine's auditLogProvider logging to PostgreSQL audit_logs table

### 1.2 RBAC (ROLE-BASED ACCESS CONTROL)

Following Slack's RBAC architecture pattern: permissions are individual abilities, roles are named collections of permissions, entities are scopes where roles apply.

ROLE DEFINITIONS:

SUPER_ADMIN (Owner/CTO level):
- All permissions across all modules
- System configuration changes
- Role assignment and delegation
- Database maintenance operations
- Feature flag management
- A/B test configuration
- Billing and revenue access
- User impersonation
- Cannot be deleted or demoted by other admins

CONTENT_MANAGER:
- Content CRUD: create, read, update, delete, approve, reject, schedule
- Content categories management
- Content preview and testing
- View content analytics (engagement rates)
- NO access to: user management, system health, billing, feature flags

SUPPORT_AGENT:
- Read-only user details (profile, tasks, projects, notification history)
- View user's sync status and device info
- Create internal notes on user accounts
- Trigger manual notification resend
- View delivery logs for specific users
- Suspend user (requires SUPER_ADMIN approval for ban)
- NO access to: content management, system config, billing, feature flags

VIEWER (Stakeholder/Investor):
- Read-only dashboards: analytics, revenue, system health
- Export reports (CSV/PDF)
- NO write access to any module
- NO access to: individual user data (PII), support tools

PERMISSION MATRIX:

| Permission               | Super Admin | Content Mgr | Support Agent | Viewer |
|--------------------------|:-----------:|:-----------:|:-------------:|:------:|
| users.list               |      Y      |      -      |       Y       |   -    |
| users.view_details       |      Y      |      -      |       Y       |   -    |
| users.suspend            |      Y      |      -      |    Y (req.)   |   -    |
| users.ban                |      Y      |      -      |       -       |   -    |
| users.change_plan        |      Y      |      -      |       -       |   -    |
| users.impersonate        |      Y      |      -      |       -       |   -    |
| users.delete             |      Y      |      -      |       -       |   -    |
| content.create           |      Y      |      Y      |       -       |   -    |
| content.approve          |      Y      |      Y      |       -       |   -    |
| content.schedule         |      Y      |      Y      |       -       |   -    |
| content.delete           |      Y      |      Y      |       -       |   -    |
| notifications.view       |      Y      |      -      |       Y       |   Y    |
| notifications.resend     |      Y      |      -      |       Y       |   -    |
| analytics.view           |      Y      |      -      |       -       |   Y    |
| analytics.export         |      Y      |      -      |       -       |   Y    |
| system.health            |      Y      |      -      |       -       |   Y    |
| system.config            |      Y      |      -      |       -       |   -    |
| flags.manage             |      Y      |      -      |       -       |   -    |
| flags.view               |      Y      |      -      |       -       |   Y    |
| audit.view               |      Y      |      -      |       -       |   -    |
| billing.view             |      Y      |      -      |       -       |   Y    |
| billing.manage           |      Y      |      -      |       -       |   -    |

IMPLEMENTATION (Refine accessControlProvider):

```typescript
// Access control provider for Refine
const accessControlProvider = {
  can: async ({ resource, action, params }) => {
    const role = getCurrentUserRole();
    const permissions = rolePermissions[role];
    const permissionKey = `${resource}.${action}`;
    
    if (permissions.includes(permissionKey) || permissions.includes('*')) {
      return { can: true };
    }
    
    return {
      can: false,
      reason: `Role "${role}" lacks permission "${permissionKey}"`,
    };
  },
};
```

