MODULE 7: FEATURE FLAGS
Route: /admin/flags

Following the 4 flag types pattern:

List View:
- Table: Flag Key, Type (Release/Experiment/Ops/Permission), Status (On/Off/Percentage), Targeting, Created By, Created At, Last Modified
- Filter by type, status, owner

Flag Detail View:
- Key (immutable after creation, naming: area_feature_type)
- Description and documentation link
- Type selector: Release | Experiment | Ops (Kill Switch) | Permission
- Global toggle: On/Off
- Targeting Rules (ordered, first match wins):
  Rule 1: If user.plan IN [pro, annual, team] -> ON
  Rule 2: If user.id IN [specific_user_ids] -> ON (beta testers)
  Rule 3: If user.industry IN [legal, healthcare] -> ON
  Rule 4: Percentage rollout: X% of remaining users -> ON
  Default: OFF
- A/B Test Configuration (for Experiment type):
  Variants: Control (A), Variant B, Variant C
  Traffic split: 50/25/25
  Primary metric: task_completion_rate
  Secondary metrics: session_duration, retention_d7
  Statistical significance threshold: 95%
  Minimum sample size: 1000 per variant
- Audit trail: who changed what, when
- Stale flag detection: flags unchanged for 30+ days get warning badge

Best Practices Enforcement:
- Max 50 active flags at any time
- Release flags auto-alert after 30 days if not at 100%
- Kill switches required on all external integrations (WhatsApp, Telegram, SMS, Email, AI)
- Naming convention enforced: {module}_{feature}_{type} (e.g., notifications_whatsapp_killswitch)

MODULE 8: AUDIT LOG
Route: /admin/audit

Table: Timestamp, Actor (admin user), Action, Resource, Resource ID, Old Value (JSON), New Value (JSON), IP Address, User Agent, Result (Success/Failure)

Filters: Actor, Action Type, Resource Type, Date Range, Result

Action Types Tracked:
- User actions: user.suspended, user.banned, user.plan_changed, user.impersonated, user.deleted
- Content actions: content.created, content.approved, content.rejected, content.scheduled, content.deleted
- System actions: flag.toggled, flag.rule_changed, alert.created, alert.resolved
- Auth actions: admin.login, admin.logout, admin.password_changed, admin.mfa_configured
- Config actions: config.changed, role.assigned, role.revoked

Retention: 2 years (compliance with India DPDP Act 2023)
Export: CSV with date range filter

Drizzle Schema for Audit Logs:

```typescript
export const auditActionEnum = pgEnum('audit_action', [
  'user.viewed', 'user.suspended', 'user.banned', 'user.reactivated',
  'user.plan_changed', 'user.impersonated', 'user.deleted',
  'content.created', 'content.updated', 'content.approved',
  'content.rejected', 'content.scheduled', 'content.deleted',
  'flag.created', 'flag.toggled', 'flag.rule_changed', 'flag.deleted',
  'alert.created', 'alert.acknowledged', 'alert.resolved',
  'admin.login', 'admin.logout', 'admin.role_changed',
  'notification.resent', 'config.changed',
]);

export const auditLogs = pgTable('audit_logs', {
  id: uuid('id').primaryKey().defaultRandom(),
  actorId: uuid('actor_id').references(() => adminUsers.id).notNull(),
  actorEmail: text('actor_email').notNull(),
  actorRole: text('actor_role').notNull(),
  action: auditActionEnum('action').notNull(),
  resourceType: text('resource_type').notNull(),   // 'user', 'content', 'flag', etc.
  resourceId: text('resource_id'),                  // UUID or identifier of affected resource
  oldValue: jsonb('old_value'),                     // Previous state (for updates)
  newValue: jsonb('new_value'),                     // New state (for updates)
  metadata: jsonb('metadata'),                      // Additional context
  ipAddress: text('ip_address'),
  userAgent: text('user_agent'),
  result: text('result').default('success').notNull(), // 'success' or 'failure'
  reason: text('reason'),                           // For failures or required justification
  createdAt: timestamp('created_at', { withTimezone: true }).defaultNow().notNull(),
}, (table) => [
  index('audit_logs_actor_idx').on(table.actorId),
  index('audit_logs_action_idx').on(table.action),
  index('audit_logs_resource_idx').on(table.resourceType, table.resourceId),
  index('audit_logs_created_at_idx').on(table.createdAt),
]);
```

