  (Using Blackbox exporter probe_success)

### 2.9 ALERT RULES

CRITICAL (Page immediately, 24/7):
- API error rate > 5% for 2 minutes
- API p99 latency > 5 seconds for 5 minutes
- Database connections > 90% of max for 5 minutes
- Queue depth > 5000 and growing for 10 minutes
- Crash-free sessions < 99% in last hour
- Notification delivery rate < 90% any channel for 15 minutes
- Redis memory > 95%
- Disk usage > 90%

WARNING (Slack notification, business hours):
- API error rate > 1% for 5 minutes
- API p95 latency > 1 second for 10 minutes
- Database connections > 70% of max
- Queue depth > 1000 for 15 minutes
- Redis hit rate < 90%
- Notification delivery rate < 95% any channel for 30 minutes
- Daily notification cost exceeds budget by 20%
- Dead letter queue > 100 jobs

INFO (Logged, daily digest):
- New version deployed
- Feature flag changed
- Daily cost summary
- Weekly retention report
- Monthly business metrics summary

### 2.10 DATA PIPELINE

Event Collection:
- Mobile App: PostHog Flutter SDK -> PostHog Cloud (or self-hosted)
- Backend: PostHog Node SDK -> PostHog (server-side events for accuracy)
- Metrics: Prometheus scraping /metrics endpoint every 15 seconds
- Errors: Sentry SDK (Flutter + Node.js) -> Sentry Cloud
- Logs: Structured JSON logs -> Loki -> Grafana

Aggregation:
- PostHog handles event aggregation internally (funnels, retention, trends)
- Prometheus recording rules for expensive queries (pre-aggregate)
- Custom daily/weekly/monthly rollup jobs in BullMQ for business metrics

Storage & Retention:
- PostHog events: 1 year (free tier: 1M events/month)
- Prometheus raw metrics: 15 days (local), 13 months (remote write to Thanos/Mimir for production)
- Sentry events: 90 days (free tier: 5K errors/month)
- Loki logs: 30 days
- Business metric rollups: Indefinite (PostgreSQL table, ~1 row per metric per day)

### 2.11 IMPLEMENTATION PRIORITY

Phase 1 (Week 1-2): Core instrumentation
- PostHog Flutter SDK + Node SDK setup
- Core events: signup, login, task CRUD, notification sent/delivered/failed
- Sentry Flutter + Node.js SDK
- Prometheus /metrics endpoint on Hono backend
- Basic Grafana dashboard (API health)

Phase 2 (Week 3-4): Dashboards
- PostHog dashboards: Executive, Activation, Engagement
- Grafana dashboards: Database, Queue
- Sentry release tracking
- Alert rules (Critical tier only)

Phase 3 (Week 5-6): Advanced
- Channel performance dashboard
- Revenue dashboard
- Feature adoption tracking
- Warning + Info alert tiers
- Recording rules for expensive queries

Phase 4 (Ongoing): Optimization
- A/B testing integration with feature flags
- Cohort analysis refinement
- Predictive churn model training data
- Cost optimization based on channel analytics

